Zen IDE bundles two third-party fonts and several open-source Python packages.

Fonts:

  1. ZenIcons.ttf — a subset of SymbolsNerdFont-Regular.ttf containing only
     the icon glyphs used by the IDE (generated via tools/subset_icon_font.py).

  2. SourceCodePro-VariableFont_wght.ttf — monospace text font from Google
     Fonts (Adobe).

Python packages:

  This application includes open-source Python packages listed in
  pyproject.toml:

    PyGObject               — LGPL-2.1  — GTK bindings for Python
    pyobjc-framework-Cocoa  — MIT       — macOS Cocoa bindings (macOS only)
    pyobjc-framework-WebKit — MIT       — macOS WebKit bindings (macOS only)
    watchfiles              — MIT       — Filesystem watcher
    PyYAML                  — MIT       — YAML parser
    cmarkgfm                — MIT       — GitHub-Flavored Markdown renderer
    psutil                  — BSD-3     — Process and system utilities
    ruff                    — MIT       — Python linter and formatter

  See each package's repository for its full license text.

